.TH "scsi_partsize" 9 "scsi_partsize" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
scsi_partsize \- Parse cylinders/heads/sectors from PC partition table
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" scsi_partsize
.BI "(struct block_device *bdev "  ","
.BI "sector_t capacity "  ","
.BI "int geom[3] "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bdev" 12
block device to parse
.IP "capacity" 12
size of the disk in sectors
.IP "geom" 12
output in form of [hds, cylinders, sectors]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Determine the BIOS mapping/geometry used to create the partition
table, storing the results in \fIgeom\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
false on failure, true on success.
